# Generator Coding Conventions

- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in every module for modern type hints
- Pydantic v2 models with `model_config = {"populate_by_name": True}` for camelCase JSON + snake_case Python
- All random generation must accept a `random.Random` instance (seeded) -- never use `random.random()` at module level
- PyArrow types are built in `schema_builder.py`, data in `data_generator.py` -- keep these concerns separate
- Complex types (LIST, MAP, STRUCT) generate recursively; scalar types dispatch through `_pick_scalar_generator`
- Null injection: REQUIRED columns never get nulls; OPTIONAL columns use `nullRatio` or `defaultNullRatio`
- `fixedValues` on a column overrides random generation (used for sentinel-collision testing)
